WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:25.000
Cricket Intelligence API starts in deterministic local mode with no external providers, enrichment, models, or ingestion.

00:25.000 --> 00:55.000
The status endpoint exposes the repository snapshot and provider capability flags without leaking a filesystem path.

00:55.000 --> 01:25.000
A real API request answers the LBW question from checked-in repository knowledge.

01:25.000 --> 01:55.000
The selected 2011 World Cup fact is returned from the curated history snapshot.

01:55.000 --> 02:25.000
The India query preserves its team response contract while clearly reporting that archive statistics are unavailable.

02:25.000 --> 02:50.000
The unconfigured live-score boundary returns HTTP 503 with an external-provider label.

02:50.000 --> 03:15.000
The API denies an untrusted origin, rejects an oversized body, adds security headers, and hides the Express signature.

03:15.000 --> 03:45.000
Nineteen routing cases and five real HTTP tests pass; the runtime dependency audit reports zero known vulnerabilities.

03:45.000 --> 04:20.000
Architecture, data provenance debt, optional adapters, and the release non-claims remain explicit.
